dc.type: Enter a type for your information product.
dc.subtype: If there is an opportunity to refine your type with an item of the subtype list, you may want to choose a subtype (this is optional). In such case the metadata requirements of the subtype will apply. What is called "subtype" can have the character of an attribute, such as "internal", "template" or "interactive" which tells the user more about the kind of usage.
peer-reviewed y/n: Please specify if the document is peer-reviewed or not.
dc.title: Please type the title of the information product.
dc.description: Please describe in few words the content of the information product and where necessary the methodology applied.
dc.subject: Please add keywords describing the subject of the information product.
dc.subject vocab=GACS/AGROVOC/CAB: Please add Agrovoc keywords describing the subject of the information product.
dc.creator: Please give the name and check the correct spelling.
dc.creator ID: Please give an ORCID identifier of that creator.
dc.creator Affiliation: Please note the organization the creator was affiliated with at time of creation.
dc.publisher: Please add the publisher. Usually a commercial publisher (like "Elsevier") or the institute of the main creator (like "IFPRI").
dc.contributor type=Project: Please add the Project name which is responsible for the creation of the information product.
dc.contributor Project Lead Center: Please add the Project Lead Center of the CRP (if applicable).
dc.contributor type=Partner: Please add the name of Partner (either organization or name). Whenever possible, use official identifier like ORCID numbers for a person or ISNI for an organization.
dc.contributor type=CRP: Please pick from the list the CRP name under which the information product was created.
dc.contributor type=Donor: Please pick from the list the name of the donor of the project.
dc.contact: Please add the contact point for this information product. Tip: use a department rather than an individual; this field is intended to provide a point of contact for anyone who has questions or needs further guidance about the dataset or information product connected to the record.
dc.contact.email: Please add the E-Mail address of the chosen contact point.
dc.date type: Please add the completion and availability dates
dc.date type=completion: Please pick the date of creation. This day marks the start of the embargo period.
dc.date type=availability: Please pick the end date of the embargo period according to the applicable data sharing policy.
dc.language: Please pick from the list the acronyms of the language contained in the information product (Default="English"). Use "Artificial languages" in case of a programming language and "No linguistic content" for an information product without linguistic content. Select "Uncoded languages" for languages without an ISO code.
dc.identifier: Please add an identifier of this information product. This may be a handle, DOI, ISSN, ISBN or the like.
dc.identifier type=bibliographiCitation: Please write the text that you want the user to cite this document.
dc.identifier type=identifier: Please add the type of identifier
dc.source: Please add the original journal or other type of material where an item was originally published, for example a journal title if the information product described is a journal article.
howpublished: Here you can give any more citation relevant details how the item was published.
booktitle: Please add the title of the larger whole containing this item. Example: a booktitle if the item described is a book chapter.
chapter: Please ad the chapter name or section number.
pages: Please add the page or pages of the reference.
number: Please add the number of the periodical or series.
edition: Please add the edition name if applicable.
notes: You may want to add any notes to the information product citation.
dc.relation: Here, you can describe relations to other information products. This helps finding and re-using content and hence increases the citation rate.
dc.relation hasFormat: If the information product as other related information products with the same content but different format, those can be specified by name or identifier.
dc.relation isFormatOf: If the information product is in a different format of an original, the original one can be specified here by name or identifier.
dc.relation hasPart: If the information product is part of a larger whole, specify this container name or even better give the identifier.
dc.relation isPartOf: If the information product contains part, you can specify this parts names or even better give the identifiers.
dc.relation hasVersion: If the information product is version of another information product, specify this other information product name or even better give the link in form of a handle or DOI.
dc.relation isVersionOf: If the information product contains part, you can specify this parts names or even better give the identifying handle or DOI.
dc.relation conformsTo: If the information product conforms to a certain information product such as a standard, please specify this information product name or even better give the identifying link in form of a handle or DOI.
dc.relation replaces: If the information product replaces another information product, please specify the replaced information product name or even better give the identifying link in form of a handle or DOI.
dc.relation isReplacedBy: If this information product is replaced by another information product, please specify the replacing information product name or even better give the identifying link in form of a handle or DOI.
dc.relation references: If this information product references another information product, please specify the referenced information product name or even better give the identifying link in form of a handle or DOI.
dc.relation isReferencedBy: If this information product is referenced by another information product, please specify the referenced information product name or even better give the identifying link in form of a handle or DOI.
dc.relation requires: If this information product requires another information product, please specify the required information product name or even better give the identifying link in form of a handle or DOI.
dc.relation isRequiredBy: If this information product is required by another information product, please specify that information product name or even better give the identifying link in form of a handle or DOI.
isMetadataFor: If this information product is containing the metadata for another information product, please specify that described information product name or even better give the identifying link in form of a handle or DOI.
dc.relation HasMetadata: If this information product uses another information product to store its metadata, please specify that information product name or even better give the identifying link in form of a handle or DOI.
dc.contributor type=person role=Editor: Please add the editor name or identifier.
dc.contributor type=person role=HostingI: Please add the name or identifier of the hosting institute of the activity described.
dc.contributor type=person role=ProjectL: Please add the name or identifier of the project leader.
dc.contributor type=person role=Producer: Please add the name or identifier of the producer(s).
dc.contributor type=person role=Data ana: Please add the name or identifier of the data analyst(s).
dc.contributor type=person role=Supervis: Please add the name or identifier of the supervisor(s).
dc.contributor type=person role=ServiceP: Please add the name or identifier of any relevant service provider.
dc.contributor type=person role=Geoinfor: Please add the name or identifier of the geoinformation specialist involved in producing the information product.
dc.contributor type=person role=translat: Please add the name or identifier of the translator(s) if applicable.
dc.contributor type=person role=other: Please add the name or identifier of any other relevant contributor.
dc.rights: Please add some rights information about the information product.
dc.accessRights: A person or organization owning or managing rights over the resource
terms of use: If there are terms of use other or beyond the license terms, please specify them here. (Examples: "non-commercial educational use only", or "Re-use (no translations)" )
dc.rightsHolder: Please add the official copyright holder.
dc.targetaudience: Please add a target audience if applicable.
event name: Please add the name of the event.
event type: Please pick the best fitting event type.
event date: Please pick the start date of the event.
dc.coverage: Please describe the temporal and spatial coverage.
dc.coverage type=Region: Please pick one or more international regions the information product relates to.
dc.coverage type=Country: Please pick one or more countries the information product relates to.
dc.coverage type=Administrative Unit: Please pick one or more national administrative units the information product relates to.
dc.coverage type=AEZ (FAO): Please pick one or more agro-ecological zones the information product is valid for.
dc.coverage type=ChronologicalPeriod eve: Please pick the coverage date if a single one.
Please pick start and end date of validity if it is a period.
dc.coverage type=geospatial X: Please give the latitude coordinate of the geospatial point(s).
dc.coverage type=geospatial Y: Please give the longitudinal coordinate of the geospatial point(s).
dc.coverage type=location name: Please enter the names of the locations. If the name matches to a geoname.org-entry, then coordinates can be taken from that database if not known.
dc.coverage type=geospatial bounding box: Please give the most northern, southern, western and eastern coordinate of the geospatial area.
dc.coverage type=geospatial reference sy: Please pick from the list the spatial reference system. (Default: "WGS84"=EPSG::4978 )
